title: For Sale/Trade:  LMT AR15 Daniel Defense Magpul
postcontent:
Better get your AR before the gun grabbers do.  Lewis  Machine and Tool. A elite maker of the AR and because with all of their gov contracts, they don't persue Citizen sales as much. However, there is a reason they are elite and top of the line. Why special? Read on:

THE BARREL

LMT is unique amongst the big box M4 clones in that their barrels are something special. Unlike a conventional M4 that is acid etched to remove a layer of metal to make room for the chrome plating, LMT's barrels are CUT slightly over-sized when they are made, and THEN chromed. This creates a much more uniform chrome lining and a much more accurate barrel. LMT's barrels are made by Mike Rock at Rock Creek, one of the most esteemed barrel makers in the business, known for quality and accuracy. You can not get a more accurate M4! 


Chryo'd:
 On top of that accuracy process, the barrels then go through another unique process of being chryogenicly frozen, which is a process only the highest quality barrels have done. This process more evenly aligns the grain of the steel at a molecular level which results in increased accuracy and longevity of the barrel. 

Enhanced Receiver Extension 



In a way the receiver extension is the heart of the rifle, if it breaks the rifle ceases to function. LMT's receiver extensions are machined from 7075 alluminum. That's not all though, they are coated with a dry film lubricant inside and out (which is the grey color you see in the picture. They also have extra drainage holes that other extensions do not have. These are two features unique to LMT. 





Tactical Charging Handle 



LMT's tactical charging handle is one of the first and in my opinion the BEST of all the charging handle designs. Unlike a lot of tactical units, it is not overly large and obtrusive to get caught up on things, or to pinch your skin when you charge it. It is low profile, yet offers a distinct advantage when compared to a standard handle.

LMT's FULL AUTO BCG 



This rifle has been upgraded to have LMT's FULL AUTO BCG. Most LMT rifles come standard with a semi auto BCG, but this one has the full auto. The bolt is made out of C-158 steel HPT and MPI'd. You will not find a higher quality BCG on the market, the LMT full auto BCGs sell for almost $200 on their own! 



Fit / Finish + Little Details: 



The LMT really has the nicest lowers in my honest opinion. The fit and finish is outstanding, but more so than that is the attention to little details. Sure, the trigger pull is very nice, but it's the unique touches that I really like. Like the magazine bolt hold open paddle? Well, it is ridged on not just the paddle portion, but also on the small lower portion. LMT is the only one that does this. Also, the selector has the same grooves all over it. Again, another feature unique to LMT. 


OK so this one and specs:
Rifle Defender Model 
Daniel Defense M4A1 RISII
Magpul BUIS
Magpul MOE stock
Tango Down pistol grip 
3 new Magpul P mags
100 rounds of PMC brass cased ammo
....and a brand new Bushnell TRS25 AR specific red dot 

Little use guess at 500 rounds 

List price is right around $2000. Without goodies. Won't last long at 1100.00!
Trades 

High end AK47 
Carry handgun and cash.

This is basically only a cheap deer gun or a parts gun for a rebuild.

title: For Sale:  '72-'76 Sterling Arms GASPORT, NY 300 .25 acp
postcontent:
The reason Gasport, NY is in all caps is to separate this one from those made in Lockport, NY.  The Gasport frames and slides were made from machined, tempered steel.  The 300 models were made in Gasport from '72-76.  When purchased and moved to Lockport, NY in '77 the frames and slides were cast w/a zinc alloy and the inspection tolerances were expanded creating an inferior product.  The Sterling 300s are American copies of the Rigarmi/Galesi .25.  A tried and true design.  The Gasport manufactured .25s are very well made.
This pistol is a fine shooter.  Very dependable.  Blued.  Comes with 2 mags and an i/owb holster.  It's a King all leather.  Parts are readily available.  Field strip is a breeze.  Plenty of 'tube videos.
Dimensions are 4.8x3.3x.8.  15 oz w/full mag.
280 rounds of Prvi Partizan PPU 50gr FMJ and 135 rounds of Sellier & Bellot 50gr FMJ as well. Carry the S&B.  Use the PPU for proficency.
So, the pistol, 2 mags, holster and 415 rounds for the asking price.
150.00 for the pistol, mags and holster
100.00 for the ammo.

title: For Sale:  Winchester Model 64 Carbine 30 WCF Lyman 56 1935
postcontent: Offered for your consideration is a fine early model 64 carbine made in 1935. Factory correct 20 inch carbine barrel with integral front sight ramp, bore is sharp and mirror bright. The barrell and magazine retain 95% original blue. The receiver is mechanically fine, feeds, fires and ejects smoothly. Headspace is perfect. Receiver has the typical mottled finish from this era, the carbona blue just never held that well on the nickle steel Winchester used in the receivers. It has the Lyman 56 receiver sight which was a factory option. The wood is solid and tight, nicely grained black walnut that has a few very minor handling marks but no chips, cracks, extra holes or bad dents. This is a fine vintage Winchester that has that "slick as glass" feel when you cycle the bolt. A rare model 64 factory carbine from an era of fine craftmanship we will probably never see again

It's a beautiful specimen.
